    <body>
      <div xml:id="NA241-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">itu talaimakaḷ vaṉpoṟai yetiraḻintatu.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is what SHE said in the face of encouragement.</p>
        </div>
      <div xml:id="NA241">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            uḷḷār kollō tōḻi koṭuñciṟai</l>
<l>            yuḷḷaṭi poṟitta variyuṭait talaiya</l>
<l>            nīraḻi maruṅki ṉīrayir tōṉṟa</l>
<l>            vaḷarā vāṭai yuḷarpunaṉi tīṇṭaliṉ</l>
<l>            vēḻa veṇpū virivaṉa palavuṭaṉ </l>
<l>            vēntuvīcu kavariyiṟ pūmputa laṇiya</l>
<l>            maḻaikaḻi vicumpiṉ māṟi ñāyiṟu</l>
<l>            viḻittimaip patupōl viḷaṅkupu maṟaiya</l>
<l>            vellai pōkiya poḻuti ṉelluṟap</l>
<l>            paṉikkāṟ koṇṭa paiyuḷ yāmattup </l>
<l>            pallita ḻuṇkaṇ kaluḻa</l>
<l>            nillāp poruṭpiṇi pirintici ṉōrē.</l>
            </lg>
        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>Won’t he remember, friend,</l>
<l>the one who separated enticed by transient wealth,</l>
<l rend="indent2">while [my] many-petalled collyrium eyes are dimming</l>
<l rend="indent2">at sorrowful midnight taken by the chilly wind,</l>
<l rend="indent3">when night falls(?) at the time the daylight is gone,</l>
<l rend="indent3">when the sun after shining vanishes, as in the winking of an eye,</l>
<l rend="indent4">having changed the sky as the rain is passing,</l>
<l rend="indent3">while the bushes adorn themselves with flowers as chowries</l>
<l rend="indent3">flung by a king,</l>
<l rend="indent3">many together, the Vēḻam’s white flowers expanding(?)<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">virivaṉa</term>: here in the row of loosely connected infinitives we have a participial noun (that looks like a finite form). How to construe (and how to justify)?</note></l>
<l rend="indent">in the inimical north wind’s whiffling [and] gripping [them] strongly(?)<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">naṉi tīṇṭaliṉ</term>: can the text be correct here (the variant is even worse)? What is the message?</note>,</l>
<l rend="indent3">while in the wet sand at a side where the water is spent appear</l>
<l rend="indent3">lined traces<note place="foot">Line 2 cannot be in order. The point is certainly, as T.V.G. explains, the footprints the birds leave in the wet sand, but a word for these traces is missing, unless we take talaiya as a neuter plural and subject of <term xml:lang="ta">tōṉṟa</term> (T.V.G. takes it vaguely as "in the area", but why mark this with an -<term xml:lang="ta">a</term> and what would be the point of telling this when there is <term xml:lang="ta">maruṅkiṉ</term>?). Still, from a semantic point of view, this is far from satisfactory.</note> impressed by the inner feet of those with bent wings?</l>
      </lg>
      </div>
